	     Cape Town – Two people were killed and two other were severely injured after two bakkies and a motorbike collided on the R101 near Franschhoek on Saturday, paramedics said. ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said when paramedics arrived at the scene, four men and a child, believed to be two, were found. Siddall said two men were declared dead at the scene. The other man and a child were taken to the Paarl Provincial Hospital for further medical care. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigation. The cause of the accident is unknown.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  